    rationale: "Sulfonamide-induced rashes can be IgE-mediated, indicating prior sensitization. Once sensitized, re-exposure to sulfonamide-containing compounds or structurally similar drugs (e.g., certain diuretics, local anesthetics with para-amino groups) can trigger mast cell degranulation and anaphylaxis. This history mandates careful drug selection and preparation for anaphylaxis management. Gut flora depletion does not directly mediate drug hypersensitivity. Trimethoprim does not inhibit histamine degradation. Sulfonamide rashes are not always non-immunologic \u2014 IgE-mediated reactions do occur and carry future risk.",
