    rationale: "At a growth rate of 0.1 mm/day, 9 mm of nail growth represents 90 days, or approximately 3 months. Beau's lines are transverse grooves that form when nail matrix cell proliferation is temporarily halted by a systemic insult (severe illness, nutritional deficiency, major surgery, or chemotherapy). The distance of the line from the nail matrix reflects the time elapsed since the insult. This calculation (distance \u00f7 0.1 mm/day) is a clinically useful tool for estimating when a systemic event occurred. 3 weeks would correspond to ~2.1 mm; 9 months to ~27 mm; 9 days to ~0.9 mm.",
